## Model Selection Guide

**For Strategy & Vision:**
- Working Backwards (customer-back thinking)
- First Principles (challenge assumptions)
- Inversion (avoid failure modes)

**For Prioritization:**
- ROI Thinking (investment vs. return)
- Cost of Delay (timing matters)
- Opportunity Cost (what are we NOT doing)

**For Growth & Retention:**
- Flywheels/Loops (sustainable growth)
- Network Effects (viral growth)
- Social Proof (adoption drivers)

**For Competitive Analysis:**
- Moats (sustainable advantage)
- Network Effects (defensibility)
- Two-Sided Markets (platform dynamics)

**For Decision-Making:**
- Second-Order Thinking (consequences)
- Cognitive Biases (avoid errors)
- Sunk Cost Fallacy (don't look back)

**For User Behavior:**
- Loss Aversion (motivation)
- Social Proof (influence)
- Cognitive Biases (predictable errors)

