## Building Your Latticework

1. **Learn one model at a time:** Don't try to memorize all 20. Learn one, apply it, then learn another.

2. **Apply to real situations:** Models are useless in theory. Use them on actual problems.

3. **Notice when models conflict:** This is where insight happens. When ROI says "go" but Inversion says "risk," dig deeper.

4. **Build your go-to set:** Most PMs have 5-7 models they use constantly. Find yours.

5. **Expand deliberately:** When you encounter a new problem type, learn the relevant model.

